==========================================================
STEP 1
MALWARE FILE ARRIVES
==========================================================

Example:

    virus.exe

or

    trojan.exe

or

    suspicious_file.exe

The file is suspected to be malicious.


==========================================================
STEP 2
CONVERT FILE TO IMAGE
==========================================================

Every file is actually a sequence of bytes.

Example:

    54 32 89 10 23 44 ...

These bytes are converted into pixels.

Example:

    Byte Value --> Pixel Brightness

Result:

    Malware Image

Different malware families create different visual patterns.


==========================================================
STEP 3
IMAGE ENTERS AI MODEL
==========================================================

Model Used:

    Vision Transformer (ViT-B/16)

This model is similar to models used for:

    Object Detection
    Medical Imaging
    Satellite Analysis

But here it learns malware patterns.


==========================================================
STEP 4
AI ANALYZES PATTERNS
==========================================================

The AI learns:

    Texture Patterns
    Structural Layouts
    Entropy Regions
    Packed Sections
    Malware Signatures

It does NOT memorize files.

It learns family characteristics.


==========================================================
STEP 5
AUGMENTATION (ANTI-EVASION TRAINING)
==========================================================

Techniques Used:

    MixUp
    CutMix

Purpose:

    Prevent AI from memorizing images.

Benefits:

    Better Generalization
    Better Detection
    More Resistant To:

        Polymorphic Malware
        Metamorphic Malware
        Packed Malware
        Obfuscated Malware


==========================================================
STEP 6
CLASSIFICATION
==========================================================

